headline: Why Fair Isaac Plunged Over 20% This Week
summary: Fair Isaac dominates credit scoring.  In addition, the director questioned the need for three separate credit scores from all the credit bureaus on mortgage applications.  Shares of credit scoring giant Fair Isaac (NYSE: FICO) slumped 21.9% this week through Friday at 2:10 p.m. ET, according to data from S&P Global Market Intelligence.
